Chief Olabode George, former national deputy chairman, Peoples Democratic  Party  (PDP) has mourned Professor Oyewusi Ibidapo-Obe, describing him as a good and honest man. The Atona Odua of Yorubaland in a condolence message released on Thursday, described Ibidapo-Obe as a good man who served as a Vice Chancellor of the University of Lagos with selfless dignity and truth. Describing  the late Professor as a friend and my brother in accordance with Yoruba cosmology, George said, ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “Oyewusi was brilliant as brilliant could be. He was a mathematician, an engineer system analyst, a professional with bristling articulated intelligence. He was a good man who served as the Vice Chancellor of the University   Of Lagos with selfless dignity, with defined purpose. with truth  and  admirable  solidify. Ryanair To Slash UK, Ireland Flights In Response To Lockdowns Fallacies Of Health Hazards Associated With 5G The former national deputy chairman said that Ibidapo-Obe was sociable, humble, gracious, full of love, instinctively  good at heart, a scholar with comprehensive largeness. “Oye will be missed where truth and wisdom are honored,” George said.